  "texts": [
    "case law, where the Court derived from Articles 47 and 41 CFREU a right to access and comment on the evidence, which also applies to administrative decisions.",
    "127 Next to automated biometric identification, several examples of automated evidence can be considered.",
    "In Germany, the immigration authority (BAMF) uses a tool for name transliteration to convert asylum applicants' names into the Latin alphabet.",
    "The BAMF also claims this technology \"helps identify the applicant's country of origin\" and supports the plausibility check of origin.",
    "128 The BAMF also uses the \"dialect identification assistance system\" (DIAS) for language identification of asylum seekers."
  ]
}